This directory contains a test generator which is capable of generating
pseudo-directed random tests using similar structure as the benchmark program

To run this test generator, 
First, 

cd ..
source link.sh
cd testGen
make clean; make DEC_DATATYPE=$DEC_DATATYPE WIDTH=$BITWIDTH

Then followed by

./TEST_GEN_ASCII.$TAX_LOC $PREFIX $NUM_RETURNS
 ** Edit inputs.txt with $PREFIX.txt **
./CONVERTER.$DEC_DATATYPE 

$PREFIX is the name of your test file
$NUM_RETURNS is the number of tax returns to be contained
in the test file
$TAX_LOC is the type of tax return (CA, NC, or FED)

When you run this program, it will generate the ascii version of this file called 
$PREFIX.txt and located in the ascii/ folder. It will also generate a binary 
version of it called $PREFIX.$DEC_DATATYPE in the bin/ directory. 
Use the binary file for the benchmark simulation and ascii output file
for your reference.
